    • Person

      public Person​(java.lang.String combinedData) throws ImpulsoryAttributeRequiredException
      Constructor of Person class. It uses unchecked casting.
      Parameters:
      combinedData - - String. Input format: idperson,name,lastname,birthdate,birthplace,home,studiedat,workplaces,films,groupcode. If an attribute needs multiple inputs, just add ";" to separate them.
      Throws:
      ImpulsoryAttributeRequiredException - - Id is the only obligatory attribute.

  • Method Details

    • getDataBlocks

      public DataBlockADT<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String>[][] getDataBlocks()
      Returns all the collection of DataBlockADT<String, String>[][] type. Inside of it there is all the information about that person. It's mainly use is for removing the person from the DataBlocks and then if the DataBlocks are left empty, they are removed from the main HashMap
      Returns:
      attributes - DataBlock<String, String>[][]

    • getAttributesRelatedDataBlocks

      public DataBlockADT<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String>[] getAttributesRelatedDataBlocks​(int attribute)
      It only returns the array of DataBlockADT<String, String> of the given attribute. This can be used to search for data neighbors.
      Parameters:
      attribute - - int. This is used for selecting which attribute do we want. The Person class has public static constants for this.
      Returns:
      DataBlockADT<String, String>[]
